  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Specifying via CLI an option from `ValidatorProposerOptions` (ie `--validators-proposer-config`)  or `ValidatorOptions` (ie `--validators-graffiti`) prevents params from `ValidatorKeysOptions` to be read via yaml config file specified via `--config-file`.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Example\r\n\r\nCLI:\r\n```bash\r\n./teku --config-file ./test.yaml --validators-graffiti test\r\n```\r\ntest.yaml\r\n```yaml\r\nvalidator-keys: [\"/etc/teku/keys:/etc/teku/secrets\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\n`validator-keys` param is ignored and teku will run as it has been never specified.\r\n\r\nby removing `--validators-graffiti test` from CLI, `validator-keys` will be read again.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Initial thought\r\nit seems it's related to how picocli initializes `ArgGroup` groups and how it will apply defaults values.\r\nSince we provide config file functionality as a default value provider, it seems that specifying an argument from a `ArgGroup` causes initialization of all its sub `ArgGroup` which then are considered initialized and no default values are provided.\r\nThe same happens if you initialize a sibling group.\r\n\r\nA solution could be to flatten all the arguments to `ValidatorOptions` but then we have rethink how to avoid duplication in `VoluntaryExitCommand`.\r\n",
